1
00:00:02,333 --> 00:00:05,667
(One year ago)

2
00:00:06,933 --> 00:00:09,300
Jaemin, this is no time
to beat around the bush.

3
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,333
Just tell me straight.

4
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:15,367
Did something... really
happen between you and him?

5
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:19,200
What are you trying to say?

6
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:22,733
Don't you know there's a petition
for you to drop out of the show?

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:26,867
That's why I'm asking. Did you really...

8
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:30,333
catch feelings for that kid?

9
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:33,267
Huh?

10
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,693
You're a contestant on a survival show.
How could you get involved with an idol?

11
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:38,733
Forget it.

12
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,867
Does a scandal like this even make sense?

13
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:42,233
Their agency...

14
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:44,200
released a statement.

15
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,433
- What did it say?
- Hyung...

16
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:47,509
They said the dating rumors
are completely fabricated.

17
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:50,100
"Our artist has been harassed
by Jaemin for a long time."

18
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:53,433
"He feels more than just bothered.
He's terrified."

19
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,833
That's what they wrote.

20
00:00:56,867 --> 00:00:58,367
Wait.

21
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:00,633
Terrified...?

22
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,143
If they go public with that...

23
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:05,000
people will probably
assume you're a stalker.

24
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:06,767
What do we do now?

25
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:12,133
Director...

26
00:01:12,233 --> 00:01:13,700
Ugh... Director.

27
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:18,933
"LOVE CLASS SEASON 3"
(EPISODE 2)

28
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:36,867
I'm fine.

29
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:43,967
Your number.

30
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,467
Hold on.

31
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:49,400
I'm not the type who just
gives his number to anyone.

32
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,233
I don't know what you think of me, but...

33
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,667
Give it.

34
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,400
Please.

35
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:00,233
You're pretty forward.

36
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,233
Hey... wait!

37
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:13,867
Hey...?

38
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:16,333
No, but...

39
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:18,533
At least clean up before you go.

40
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:21,633
And is it right to just get
my number and run off?

41
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:24,433
You should at least
leave me your number too.

42
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,233
Fighting!

43
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,433
(One year ago)
Fighting!

44
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:55,933
What's this?

45
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,600
It's my good luck bracelet.

46
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:02,033
I've passed every audition I've worn it to.

47
00:03:02,133 --> 00:03:03,700
That's why I always wear it.

48
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,067
Really?

49
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:06,400
You want to try it on?

50
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,700
Can I?

51
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,333
It's almost time to go on stage.

52
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,733
Let's go.

53
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:28,767
Hyunjae, who were you talking to?

54
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:30,100
Is something wrong?

55
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,533
It's nothing.

56
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:39,233
Hello?

57
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:40,633
Hello?

58
00:03:41,033 --> 00:03:43,500
Um... well...

59
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:45,667
Just now...

60
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,200
I'm over here.

61
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,333
I didn't realize you were so close.

62
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,433
Yeah.

63
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:57,967
This is for you.

64
00:03:58,533 --> 00:04:00,033
What is it?

65
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,500
Just take it.

66
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:03,500
What is it?

67
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,867
A T-shirt.

68
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:06,200
A T-shirt?

69
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:08,600
It's okay.

70
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,533
I'm sorry.

71
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:12,167
It's really okay.

72
00:04:12,267 --> 00:04:13,833
I really don't mind.

73
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:14,967
Just take it.

74
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,900
If you're really sorry...

75
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,967
you can just buy me a meal.

76
00:04:20,067 --> 00:04:21,600
Take it.

77
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:25,100
Hey, wait.

78
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,333
I need to know your name
so I can save you as a contact.

79
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,033
(Ketchup)

80
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:49,900
Good work.

81
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,500
Good work.

82
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:58,090
(More endless "Good work!")

83
00:05:11,795 --> 00:05:12,795
Sorry.

84
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,867
Good work.

85
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,300
(Yeeun calling)

86
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:42,509
Hey, Yoon Sooan, are
you trying to get killed?

87
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:44,867
Get over here right now,
while I'm still being nice.

88
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:46,533
I can't.

89
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:48,073
Why aren't you answering your phone?

90
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:49,567
Hey, where are you?

91
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:51,267
At home.

92
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:52,367
What?

93
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,633
I met him.

94
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:17,833
You should start practicing again.

95
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,267
How can I be an idol?

96
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:22,900
Why not? You didn't do anything wrong.

97
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,667
You never should have
quit in the first place.

98
00:06:26,367 --> 00:06:28,033
You should have cleared things up.

99
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,500
That guy was the one who pursued you.

100
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,700
How could he call you a stalker?

101
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,233
That bastard.

102
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,433
I think I saw Sooan today.

103
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:53,600
At the broadcast station.

104
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:57,333
I think he's working
there as a staff member.

105
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,167
What are you talking about?

106
00:06:59,267 --> 00:07:01,533
He was the ace of Unicorn.

107
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:03,433
There's no way he'd
be working a regular job.

108
00:07:04,233 --> 00:07:05,700
Why don't you try contacting him?

109
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:12,387
[Banal couple talk above, followed by:]
(Sooan, do you have a minute to talk?)

110
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,700
Is this really okay?

111
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:40,167
What's wrong? What is it?

112
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:41,547
Hey, where'd you get that shirt?

113
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,933
Isn't that a designer brand?

114
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:44,500
No, it's not.

115
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:45,933
Yes, it is.

116
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,633
This is super expensive.

117
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:48,967
Really?

118
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:50,507
Did you blow all your money on this?

119
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:51,567
No.

120
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:52,676
Then what? Did you steal it?

121
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:53,700
Of course not.

122
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:54,967
Then where'd you get it?

123
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:58,133
How much is this thing anyway?

124
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,367
Crap.

125
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:05,900
850,000 won?

126
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,433
850,000 won.

127
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:09,700
Hey, what do I do?

128
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,800
What?

129
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,433
Wait, this won't do.

130
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:22,400
I can probably return it, right?

131
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:28,200
(PNJS Entertainment)

132
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,500
You're here.

133
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,933
If it isn't our big star.

134
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:37,333
I'm back.

135
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,600
You've worked hard.

136
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:40,767
Thank you.

137
00:08:40,867 --> 00:08:43,300
We're all looking forward to your comeback.

138
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:46,033
We have a big project starting soon.

139
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,333
Get some rest for now.

140
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:49,133
Director Park, please take Hyunjae home.

141
00:08:49,233 --> 00:08:50,667
Yes, sir.

142
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,100
Let's go.

143
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:57,533
What, you have plans to meet someone?

144
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,333
No, it's just...

145
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,976
You know that you can't slack off just
because group promotions are over, right?

146
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,967
A lot of people are watching you right now.

147
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:06,500
Yes, I understand.

148
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,933
Let's go.

149
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:17,667
The number you have dialed is not available.
Please leave a message after the beep.

150
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,567
Why isn't he picking up?

151
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,633
Hey.

152
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,600
Hey, student.

153
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:03,433
(Unicorn Entertainment)

154
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,600
(Notice of end of contract)

155
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:01,100
I've been practicing like crazy
so I could stand on the same stage as you.

156
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:14,233
Hey!

157
00:11:18,133 --> 00:11:19,600
Hey!

158
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:25,133
Hello.

159
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,600
Did I scare you?

160
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:29,733
That was a big reaction.

161
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:31,133
You scared me too.

162
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,300
I actually wanted to ask...

163
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,333
Is this T-shirt expensive?

164
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,800
Expensive?

165
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:41,267
Uh... not really.

166
00:11:42,133 --> 00:11:43,733
Not really?

167
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:45,433
I'm sorry.

168
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,367
Sorry for what?

169
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:49,000
You don't like it?

170
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,067
This shirt is expensive.

171
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:54,800
It's too expensive, you get it?

172
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,767
It's okay.

173
00:11:58,867 --> 00:12:01,200
I really don't mind about the shirt.

174
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,600
But...

175
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,500
You should return it.

176
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,000
Return it?

177
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,267
Refund, you know?

178
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,633
But...

179
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,467
I barely wore it.

180
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:15,200
It's practically new.

181
00:12:18,667 --> 00:12:19,667
What?

182
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,267
Crap.

183
00:12:25,033 --> 00:12:26,300
You should eat too.

184
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:28,900
Damn it.

185
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,400
Kim Hyunjae...

186
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,967
What do I do now?

187
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:38,300
It's okay.

188
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,833
No...

189
00:12:40,767 --> 00:12:43,000
I hate being indebted to people.

190
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,333
What I can give you right now...

191
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,767
isn't much, I guess.

192
00:12:51,867 --> 00:12:53,200
I have to do something.

193
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,800
With your body.

194
00:12:58,633 --> 00:13:00,067
Sorry?

195
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,300
Then pay me back... with your body.

196
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:27,567
Stay tuned for LOVE CLASS 3.

197
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,309
(PREVIEW, EPISODE 3)
(LUXE HOTEL)

198
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,133
This isn't right.

199
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:33,433
What the hell is that guy thinking?

200
00:13:33,533 --> 00:13:36,233
Don't tell me he left this
for me to see on purpose.

201
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,033
Why did you suddenly ghost me?

202
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,776
You just used me as a
stepping stone, didn't you?

203
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,833
You've already debuted.
Isn't that enough for you?

204
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:45,367
Want me to heat this up for you?

205
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:50,433
Do you really not feel
anything for me at all?

